- what it was
- when/where that happened
- how you broke it
- explain what you did after that

I’d like to talk about a time when I accidentally broke something important.

A couple of years ago, I broke my mother’s favorite ceramic vase at home. It was a special gift from her close friend, so it meant a lot to her.

It happened one Sunday morning when I was cleaning the living room. While I was dusting the shelves, I accidentally knocked the vase with my elbow, and it fell to the floor and broke into pieces. At that moment, I was really shocked and didn’t know what to do.

When my mom came in and saw it, I felt very nervous because I thought she would be angry. However, she stayed calm and told me that accidents happen. Even though she was a bit upset, she appreciated that I told her the truth.

After that, I tried to make her feel better by buying her some flowers later that day. Luckily, it helped improve her mood.

Overall, this experience taught me to be more careful and to take responsibility for my actions.
